---

- **Rate limit headers** – include X-RateLimit-Limit, X-RateLimit-Remaining, X-RateLimit-Reset.
- **Tiered rate limiting** – different limits for different endpoints (GET vs POST/PUT/DELETE).
- **User-based quotas** – prepare for per-user or per-API-key rate limiting.
- **Sliding window algorithm** – implement or prepare for sliding window rate limiting.
- **Graceful degradation** – return 429 Too Many Requests with retry-after header.
- **Bypass mechanisms** – prepare for rate limit exemptions for trusted clients.
- **Rate limit monitoring** – track and alert on rate limit violations and patterns.
